Miocene and Pliocene fossils of marine mammals, as well as (to a lesser extent) Late Pleistocene fossils of terrestrial and marine mammals, are known from the Westerschelde (
Drees 1986
; 

Ebbing 
et al
. 1993

). Th e Miocene and Pliocene fossils originate from the Antwerpen Sand Member (Middle Miocene), the Deurne Sand Member (Late Miocene), the Kattendijk Sand Member (Early Pliocene), the Luchtbal Sand Member (late Early Pliocene) and the Oorderen Sand Member (Middle Pliocene) and are reworked from these strata by the eroding river Schelde (
Drees 1986
; 

Ebbing 
et al
. 1993

).

Taking all evidence into account, an Early Pliocene (Zanclean; between 5.0 Ma and 4.7-4.4 Ma; 

Louwye 
et al
. 2004

) origin of this cranium is assumed.
